This paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for biomedical data processing, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the issue of confounding variables in supervised classification problems, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
